The paper deals with the entropy of patterns of sequences generated by i.i.d. sources, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of patterns also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and pattern matching algorithms. The paper also presents bounds on the entropy, which involves probability theory and combinatorics, making it relevant to information theory and probability (cs.ITP, cs.LG). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) as it deals with approximations and assessing the decrease of entropy.
